</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF1682C447E3467B800FE0E" authority="Kimmins 1953" authorityName="Kimmins" authorityYear="1953" box="[291,635,363,388]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF1682C447E3467BBA6FE0E" box="[291,477,364,387]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">Ecnomina spinosa</emphasis>
Kimmins 1953
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF1682C47F93467B9D0FE0E" author="Mosely, M. E. &amp; Kimmins, D. E." box="[676,939,363,388]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" refId="ref15209" refString="Mosely, M. E. &amp; Kimmins, D. E. (1953) The Trichoptera of Australia and New Zealand. British Museum (Natural History), London, 550 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 118696" type="book" year="1953">Mosely &amp; Kimmins 1953</bibRefCitation>
), by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF1682C45CA34B9BAB9FDB5" blockId="4.[151,1436,434,568]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
The Australasian genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF1682C44FA34B8B862FE41" box="[423,537,435,460]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF1682C44FA34B8B862FE41" box="[423,537,435,460]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">Ecnomina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diverse and widespread in 
<collectingCountry id="F34961BCFFF1682C463734B9B9AFFE41" box="[874,980,434,460]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">Australia</collectingCountry>
, with 36 described species, but is represented by only a single species in each of 
<collectingCountry id="F34961BCFFF1682C472234DDB96CFE7D" box="[639,791,470,496]" name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F34961BCFFF1682C460F34DDBE79FE7D" box="[850,1026,470,496]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF1682C414F34DDBEA8FE7D" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[1042,1235,470,496]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref14639" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2008) A review of the Australian species of Ecnomina Kimmins and Daternomina Neboiss (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 1774 (1), 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1774.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Cartwright 2008</bibRefCitation>
). One established species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF1682C45AB34F0B84BFD99" authority="Cartwright 2008" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2008" box="[246,560,506,532]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF1682C45AB34F0BB0AFD99" box="[246,369,507,532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">E. concava</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF1682C442534F1B84BFD99" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[376,560,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref14639" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2008) A review of the Australian species of Ecnomina Kimmins and Daternomina Neboiss (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 1774 (1), 1 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1774.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Cartwright 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
plus the following new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFF1682C46C634F0BE65FD99" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[923,1054,506,532]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radonica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF1682C46C634F0BE65FD99" box="[923,1054,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">E. radonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF1682C417834F1BE05FD99" bold="true" box="[1061,1150,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFF1682C417834F1BE05FD99" box="[1061,1150,506,532]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, are here recorded for the NT.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
